Benjamin C. Pierce ([[WikiPedia:Benjamin C. Pierce]]) studies types and programming languages, but hacked Emacs in the early 1990s.  Some notable packages include:

* SpreadMode
* uuinsert
* reportmail

He also developed Unison, a free software file synchronization tool written in OCaml. (See [[WikiPedia:Unison (file synchronizer)]]).

* [http://www.cis.upenn.edu/~bcpierce/ Benjamin C. Pierce home page]

